# Backend Production Standards

## Module Structure (enforced)

```
expense-tracking-backend/
  common-library/               # Shared: DTOs, exceptions, security, event system, Feign interfaces
    com.jaya.common.
      config/                   # Auto-config, Kafka, Eureka, Feign, Async, Mail
      dto/                      # Shared DTOs (UserDTO, CategoryDTO)
      dto/response/             # ApiResponse, ApiError, PaginationInfo
      event/                    # EventPublisher, KafkaEventPublisher, InMemoryEventPublisher
      exception/handler/        # GlobalExceptionHandler, JpaExceptionHandler, FeignExceptionHandler
      security/                 # JwtUtil, JwtAuthenticationFilter
      service/client/           # I*ServiceClient interfaces
      service/client/feign/     # @FeignClient implementations
      service/client/local/     # Monolith-mode implementations
  {ServiceName}/                # Each microservice module
    com.jaya.
      controller/               # REST controllers (one per domain aggregate)
      dto/                      # Service-specific DTOs (Request, Response, Event)
      mapper/                   # Entity <-> DTO mapping
      models/                   # JPA entities
      repository/               # Spring Data JPA interfaces
      service/                  # Service interfaces
      service/impl/             # Service implementations
      service/helper/           # Complex business logic helpers
      service/strategy/         # Strategy pattern implementations
      kafka/                    # Kafka producers
      kafka/consumer/           # Kafka consumers
      util/                     # Service-specific utilities
      config/                   # Service-specific configuration
  eureka-server/                # Service discovery
  Gateway/                      # API Gateway + routing
  monolithic-service/           # All-in-one for local development
```

Rules:
- Every new class goes in the correct package -- no dumping code in root package
- Shared code goes in `common-library` -- never duplicate across services
- Each service is a self-contained Maven module with its own `pom.xml`
- No circular dependencies between modules

## SOLID Principles (enforced)

### Single Responsibility
- Controllers: HTTP mapping and input validation only
- Services: Business logic only (no HTTP, no direct DB queries outside repository)
- Repositories: Data access only (no business logic)
- Each class has one reason to change

### Open/Closed
- Use Strategy pattern for varying business rules (e.g., `ExpenseCalculationStrategy`)
- Use interfaces for service contracts -- add new implementations without modifying existing code
- Use `@ConditionalOnProperty` / `@Profile` to swap implementations by environment

### Liskov Substitution
- Feign clients and local clients both implement the same `I*ServiceClient` interface
- `@Profile("!monolithic")` for Feign; `@Profile("monolithic")` for local -- interchangeable

### Interface Segregation
- Define focused service interfaces (e.g., `ExpenseCoreService`, `ExpenseQueryService`, `ExpenseReportService`)
- Do not create bloated god-interfaces with 20+ methods -- split by concern

### Dependency Inversion
- Depend on abstractions (interfaces), not concrete classes
- Constructor injection only -- no field injection with `@Autowired` for new code
- Existing `@Autowired` fields are legacy; migrate when touching the class

## Design Patterns in Use

| Pattern | Where | Example |
|---------|-------|---------|
| Strategy | Expense calculation | `ExpenseCalculationStrategy` + `StandardExpenseCalculationStrategy` |
| Repository | Data access | `ExpenseRepository extends JpaRepository` |
| DTO/Mapper | API boundary | `ExpenseMapper` converts Entity <-> DTO |
| Observer | Cross-service events | `EventPublisher` + Kafka/InMemory implementations |
| Builder | Object creation | Lombok `@Builder` on DTOs and entities |
| Template Method | Exception handling | `BaseException` hierarchy + `GlobalExceptionHandler` |
| Facade | Complex operations | `ExpenseMainService` delegates to `CoreService`, `QueryService`, etc. |
| Adapter | Dual-mode deployment | `FeignClient` (microservice) / `Local` (monolith) adapters |

## DRY Principles

### What Goes in `common-library`

| Artifact | Location | When |
|----------|----------|------|
| Shared DTOs | `common.dto` | Used by 2+ services |
| Domain events | `common.event` | Published by one service, consumed by another |
| Exception classes | `common.exception` | Thrown by any service |
| Security filters | `common.security` | Applied to all services |
| Service client interfaces | `common.service.client` | Called across services |
| Configuration beans | `common.config` | Shared config (Kafka, Eureka, Async) |

### DRY Violations to Watch For

| Smell | Fix |
|-------|-----|
| Same DTO in 2+ services | Move to `common-library/dto/` |
| Same exception handling in controllers | Use `GlobalExceptionHandler` from common-library |
| Same Kafka config in multiple services | Use `CommonKafkaConfig` from common-library |
| Same validation logic in 2+ services | Extract to `common-library/util/` |
| Copy-pasted entity mapping code | Create a `@Component` mapper class |

## API Standards

- All endpoints return `ApiResponse<T>` wrapper (success, data, message, timestamp)
- All request bodies validated with `@Valid` + Bean Validation annotations
- All endpoints documented with `@Operation` + `@ApiResponse` (SpringDoc OpenAPI)
- HTTP status codes: 200 read, 201 create, 204 delete, 400 validation, 401 unauth, 403 forbidden, 404 not found, 500 internal
- Error responses use `ApiError` with errorCode, message, status, path, serviceName

## Kafka Messaging Standards

- Topic names as constants in the service class or a shared constants file
- Event classes in `common-library` for producer/consumer contract
- Producer: serialize to JSON with `ObjectMapper`, log on success and failure
- Consumer: `@KafkaListener` with explicit `groupId` including service name, `containerFactory`
- Consumers must be idempotent -- handle duplicate events gracefully
- Never put full entity objects in events -- use IDs + event type only

## Exception Handling

- All exceptions extend `BaseException` from common-library
- Never catch and swallow exceptions silently -- at minimum, log them
- Never throw generic `RuntimeException` -- use domain-specific exceptions
- `GlobalExceptionHandler` handles everything -- controllers never catch exceptions
- Validation errors return field-level detail from `MethodArgumentNotValidException`

## Logging Standards

- Use `@Slf4j` (Lombok) -- never `System.out.println` or raw `Logger` instantiation
- INFO: State changes (created, updated, deleted, published event)
- WARN: Recoverable issues (cache miss, retry, degraded response)
- ERROR: Failures requiring attention (exception, Kafka failure, DB connection error)
- Never log: passwords, JWT tokens, full credit card numbers, PII without masking
- Include context: `log.info("Created expense id={} for user={}", id, userId)`

## Environment Configuration (12-Factor Compliance)

- All config via environment variables or Spring `application.yml` with `${}` placeholders
- Never hard-code: database URLs, Kafka brokers, service URLs, secrets, ports
- Default fallbacks for local development: `${SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL:jdbc:mysql://localhost:5000/expense_tracker}`
- Profiles: `microservices` (default), `monolithic` (single JAR), `test` (H2 + embedded Kafka)
- Secrets via env vars at deployment time, never in `application.yml` or committed `.properties`

## Build Readiness Checklist

Before any backend feature is considered complete:

- [ ] No `System.out.println` -- use `@Slf4j`
- [ ] All methods under 20 lines
- [ ] All public service methods have an interface contract
- [ ] `@Valid` on every `@RequestBody`
- [ ] `@Transactional` on writes, `@Transactional(readOnly = true)` on reads
- [ ] DTOs used in responses -- never raw entities
- [ ] Exceptions flow to `GlobalExceptionHandler` -- no catch blocks in controllers
- [ ] OpenAPI annotations on every endpoint
- [ ] No hard-coded secrets, URLs, or ports
- [ ] Kafka events are idempotent with minimal payload
- [ ] Constructor injection for new code
- [ ] `mvn clean package -DskipTests` builds without errors
- [ ] No circular dependencies between modules
- [ ] Shared code lives in `common-library`, not duplicated
- [ ] Entity has audit fields (createdAt, updatedAt) with `@PrePersist` / `@PreUpdate`
